                    <tr>
           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white">
                      <font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> whoever posted the link to this discussion thanks:<br /><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=21099.topic" target="_blank">http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=21099.topic</a><br /><br /><br />Quote:<br />I was just talking in another thread about how useless Enchanter DoTs are (it was brought up as something enchanters can do in combat) and while crunching numbers to show exactly how useless they are I started comparing Damage over Time spells and am just shocked at the recent trend.<br /><br />Here are some stats in EQ Classic Era (back when Geoffery Zatkin was in charge of spells and had a very clear vision of what was going on):<br /><br />Necro :<br />Ignite Blood 1176 damage 250 mana 2.1 mins 4.74 Ratio<br /><br />Enchanter:<br />Gasping Embrace 700 damage 200 mana 2.0 mins 3.5 Ratio<br /><br />Magician: <br />Rain of Swords (assume 3 waves) 972 damage 375 mana 7.5 seconds 2.6 Ratio <-- was balanced back when rains could hit more targets and never changed  <br /><br />Wizard:<br />Frost Storm (assume 3 waves) 750 damage 312 mana 7.5 seconds duration 2.4 Ration <--- same problem as mages<br /><br />By comparison in this era the most efficient DDs were IceComet and Rend which had a 2.8 Ratio!<br /><br /><br />Kunark era:<br /><br />Necro :<br />Pyrocuror 1998 damage 400 mana 1.8 minute duration 4.995 ratio<br /><br />Splurt 1600ish damage 237 mana 1.6 minute duration 6.75 ratio<br /><br />Enchanter:<br />Aspyxiate 1010 damage 250 mana 2.0 minute duration 4.04 ratio<br /><br />Magician:<br />Manastorm 2025 damage 427 mana 7.5 second duration 4.74 ratio<br /><br />Wizard:<br />Tears of Prexus 2070 damage 437 mana 7.5 second duration 4.73 ratio<br /><br />In the Kunark era Necro DoTs get more mana efficient (especially splurt!) and also work faster than in Classic EQ. Enchanter DoTs get more efficient but still slow. Rain spells come into their own as very fast AND very efficient means to do damage.<br /><br />Most efficient DD in the Kunark era is Sunstrike at 3.58. Not only a large increase in magnitude over Classic EQ nukes but a BIG change in efficiency! The Draught spells arent much less efficient and are very common.<br /><br />Velious/Luclin era:<br /><br />Necro:<br />Funeral Pyre of Kelador 2160 damage 450 mana 54 second duration 4.8 ratio<br /><br />Enchanter:<br />Same as Kunark<br /><br />Magician:<br />Maelstrom of Electricity 2025 damage 475 mana 7.4 second duration 4.4 ratio<br /><br />Wizard:<br />Same as Kunark<br /><br />We see in the modern era a lack of DoTs and while they are hititng harder and taking less time to do it (in the necro case) the ratio is dropping. Rain spells arent as efficient but are clearly catching up to longer lasting DoTs rapidly.<br /><br />The most efficient semi-common DD in this era is the Ice Spear of Solist at 4.0 ratio, with the rare Ancient Destruction of Ice topping the scales at 4.8 making it more efficient than even the best ClassicEQ DoT.<br /><br />Planes of Power era<br /><br />Necro:<br />Dark Plague 1900 damage 300 mana 2.0 mins duration 6.3 ratio<br /><br />Blood of Thule 1605 damage 420 mana 42 second duration 3.82 ratio<br /><br />Enchanter:<br />Strangle 1575 damage 375 mana 2.0 min duration 4.2 ratio<br /><br />Magician:<br /><br />Maelstrom of Thunder 3200 damage 800 mana 7.5 second duration 4.0 ratio<br /><br />Wizard:<br />Tears of Ro 2250 damage 540 mana 7.5 second duration<br />4.17 ratio<br /><br />The most efficient DD's of the PoP era remain the Ice spear and Ancient Ice spear nukes, however of the new expansion 800 damage Draughts at 3.72 ratio are presumed to be fairly common and hard to resist.<br /><br />Necro DoTs are faster than ever but with horrible efficiency except for the MUCH longer duration Dark Plague. That Blood of Thule cannot beat the efficiency of a DD spell is disturbing. Rain spells deal hammering damage over a short duration and with extreme efficiency.<br /><br />It seems that as we move further and further from Classic EQ the Damage over Time spells are becoming progresively weaker when compared to the SHORT duration rain spells and even the instant DDs. A 2.0 minute DoT should always have a ratio at least 2 points greater than the most efficient instant spell...if not 1.5 times the efficiency as was the case in Classic EQ. That the Blood of Thule takes several times as long to work as a Rain spell and is LESS efficient is just not right.<br /><br />Its fine if you dont want the magnitude of the Necro (and Enchanter) long lasting DoTs to be comparable to Magician and Wizard raw power, but they should at least be much more efficient at what they do to account for the time involved.<br /><br />--- <br /><br />another good response in that thread:<br /><br />Fact #1: Rains resist... Rains resist a lot even on fully debuffed mobs.<br /><br />Fact #2: Dots are only slightly more effecient than nukes but usually draw more aggro for their damage (1200 damage from dots is > 1200 damage from ice spear, in the end)<br /><br />Fact #3: Necros are sorely falling behind in magical damage on short term, long term, group, and solo conditions. Soloing their advantage lies in pet/arch lich, both reduced greatly in a group, and nearly to nill on a raid.<br /><br />Fact #4: Dots have a DPS cap. Nukes have a dps cap. Dots can stay at their cap for a lot longer than nukes can stay at their cap.<br /><br />Fact #5: While dots can stay at their cap LONGER than nukes can, dots doing their max dps is comparable to nukes doing 1/3 their max dps. <-- Flaw<br /><br />Fact #6: By doing 1/3 the max dps in nukes, you can outdamage Dots for a longer period of time. When nukes outdamage dots over a long fight, this is bad <-- Flaw explanation.<br /><br />The reason for this flaw is because VI got stupid and made EVERY fight a LONG fight. If they made wizards useless over long fights, then the class would become useless in the end game. If they made necros do more and more damage the longer the fight goes on, then necros would be the most damaging class in the game.<br /><br />As it stands, wizards are the most damaging caster.. period. Necros don't hold a candle, short fight or long, and this is bad. What VI needs to implement is a variety of fights, from 2 minutes to 15 minutes, no longer PLEASE. They then need to tune wizards to be the best from the 2-8/10 mark, and necros to be the best 10+. Necros should catch up as the fight wears on but, I stress this, they shouldn't be useless in a short fight.<br /><br />Essentially, the wizard gets to do his damage 'first' and the necro gets to do his damage 'last', what needs to be avoided is the necro reaching his potential (being almost as good as the wizard) happen next to none. There's ways to do this. Dots that start their damage strong (Reverse splurt) and fade away are a good idea. These are tuned by the ability to NOT overwrite your own dot (hence reapplying the strong segment) and being incredibly effecient. Give necros a host of these dots, vs varying resists and to different degrees. It's the same as giving wizards various ratio nukes - they have to decide which to use based on fight length. For long fights, run with the splurt idea, it's a VERY GOOD IDEA. Make 10 minute 'splurts' that are DEVASTATING once they reach their 8 min+ mark. Make very long duration 'fire and forget' spells that can be depended on to sustain 10 dps for a long long fight without having to reapply (the essence of effeciency).<br /><br />I've rambled, sorry, but this topic is a sore point for me, and I hope I made *some* sense. And btw, I use necros because they're the primary dot casters, necros encs and now mages, I'm talking to you, too. <br /><br />---<br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
